  "html_url": "https://github.com/algolia/instantsearch/issues/2375",
  "title": "cssunminifier makes dist/instantsearch.css breaks all css if minified",
  "body": "https://github.com/algolia/instantsearch.js/blob/613a6155228d38accab4560ec18da852e08f59fd/scripts/build.sh#L10\r\nIt makes all the code after background-image unusable. Just ran into this, quite surprising.\r\n```css\r\n .ais-search-box--powered-by-link{background-image:url('data:image/svg+xml;utf8,<svg></svg>');vertical-align:middle;}\r\n```\r\nis converted to:\r\n```css\r\n .ais-search-box--powered-by-link {\r\n    background-image: url('data:image/svg+xml;\r\n    utf8, <svg></svg>');\r\n    vertical-align: middle;\r\n}\r\n```\r\nhttps://mrcoles.com/blog/css-unminify/\r\nif it is re-minified:\r\n```css\r\n .ais-search-box--powered-by-link{image:url('data:image/svg+xml;\r\nutf8,<svg></svg>');vertical-align:middle;}\r\n```\r\nCf. https://github.com/mrcoles/cssunminifier/issues/2\r\n\r\n**Bug: What browsers are impacted? Which versions?**\r\nAll?\r\n\r\n**What is the version you are using? Always use the latest one before opening a bug issue.**\r\nLatest: 2.1.4",
